He goes undercover as a partner with a vicious outlaw who is a contact man with the Comancheros and knows the whereabouts of their hideout in Mexico. Director Michael Curtiz's last film. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Rio Bravo
programme.desc: In 1860s Texas, a small-town county sheriff, his cantankerous old deputy, an alcoholic lawman and a young gunslinger try to keep a murderous thug jailed long enough for the U.S. marshal to arrive on the scene. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Searchers
programme.desc: When Comanches murder his brother and sister-in-law and kidnap his two nieces, a rootless, bigoted Confederate veteran teams with a young ranch hand and undertakes a perilous five-year quest to find the girls. Niece Debbie as a youngster is played by Lana Wood, while her sister Natalie portrays the older Debbie. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Cowboys
programme.desc: When his regular crew abandons him and sets out to strike gold, a veteran rancher attempts a 400-mile cattle drive with a crew of inexperienced schoolboys. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Fury
programme.desc: When a devious plot separates CIA agent Peter Sandza from his son, Robin, the distraught father manages to see through the ruse. Taken because of his psychic abilities, Robin is being held by Ben Childress, who is studying people with supernatural powers in hopes of developing their talents as weapons. Soon Peter pairs up with Gillian, a teen who has telekinesis, to find and rescue Robin. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Chosen
programme.desc: Kirk Douglas plays an industrialist who suspects that his son (Simon Ward) is plotting nuclear apocalypse. Agostina Belli, Anthony Quayle. Eva: Virginia McKenna. Meyer: Alexander Knox. Harbin: Spiros Focas. Priest: Adolfo Celi. Charrier: Romolo Valli. Originally titled "Holocaust 2000." Directed by Alberto De Martino.(n)

programme.title: Brubaker
programme.desc: A new inmate at a run-down Southern prison witnesses several instances of gross misconduct and corruption, later revealing to the guards and administrators that he's not a criminal at all, but the new warden, assigned by the governor to infiltrate the facility undercover. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Seven-Ups
programme.desc: A tough detective who is part of an elite New York City unit is trying to find out who killed his partner, but uncovers a plot to kidnap mobsters for money. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Holiday Affair
programme.desc: A department-store clerk meets a war widow who's shopping at Christmastime and romance ensues, much to the displeasure of her stuffed-shirt attorney boyfriend. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: A Chump at Oxford
programme.desc: Stan Laurel and Oliver Hardy, up to their usual antics, as two zanies creating mayhem at England's venerable university. Meredith: Forester Harvey. Banker: Forbes Murray. Servant: Frank Baker. Williams: Wilfred Lucas. Ghost: Eddie Borden. Directed by Alfred Goulding. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Blondie for Victory
programme.desc: Blondie organizes Housewives of America to perform home-front wartime duties, including guarding the local dam... Blondie for Victory was twelfth in Columbia's series of comedy films based on Chic Young's popular comic strip Blondie. Anxious to do her bit for the war effort, Blondie joins the Housewives of America, a home defense league. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: My Favorite Wife
programme.desc: A woman returns home to her husband and their children after being marooned on a desert island for seven years. But she has been declared legally dead, and he now has a second wife. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Lady in Cement
programme.desc: Private eye Tony Rome (Frank Sinatra) investigates the case of a woman found drowned off Miami Beach. Kit: Raquel Welch. Gronsky: Dan Blocker. Santini: Richard Conte. Al: Martin Gabel. Maria: Lainie Kazan. Hal: Pat Henry. Paul: Steven Peck. Audrey: Virginia Wood. Arnie: Richard Deacon. Filmed on location. Directed by Gordon Douglas. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Bullitt
programme.desc: A lone-wolf San Francisco police detective tracks syndicate killers after failing to protect a mob informant, while an ambitious senator strives to shut down his investigation. Features one of the screen's all-time great car chases. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: No Mercy
programme.desc: Richard Gere as a Chicago cop searching for his partner's killer in the bayou. Michel: Kim Basinger. Losado: Jeroen Krabbe. Stemkowski: George Dzundza. Ryan: Ray Sharkey. Richard Pearce directed. (Repeat).(n)
